The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
Archives
 Corporate Briefs
																								 Naveen Jindal-led Jindal Steel amp; Power will split each equity share of Rs 5 into five equity shares of Re 1 each. The board of directors has passed the resolution, which is subject to shareholders approval, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.																								 Wipro Technologies, the global it services business of Wipro, and ge Fanuc Intelligent Platforms, a unit of ge Enterprise, have joined hands to offer solutions for consumer products and pharmaceutical firms in production management.																								 DLF Ltd has sold a 49 per cent stake in its seven residential projects in Chennai, Bangalore, Kochi and Indore to Merrill Lynch amp; Co for Rs 1,481 crore. The realty firm also diluted a 49 per cent equity in another middle-income housing project at Panchkula in Haryana to Brahma Investments for Rs 194 crore.																								 After the carehomes project in Bangalore, LIC Housing Finance plans to develop similar cluster homes for senior citizens in other cities over the next two years. The cities where the housing projects will come up include Bhubaneswar, Chandigarh, Jaipur and Kochi.																								 UTI Asset Management Company aims to double its assets under management to Rs 70,000 crore by the end of this fiscal. As on October 31, 2007, the company had assets under management worth Rs 51,753 crore, compared with Rs 35,000 crore in the last fiscal.																								 GETIT Infoservices Ltd, an Indian yellow pages firm, in association with Fonemine Inc of the US, has launched its mobile local search offering. The site is available on www.getit.in or wap.ge-tit.in and can be accessed from mobiles having GPRS connectivity.																								 Microsoft has launched the Microsoft Office Professional 2007 prepaid edition in the country. It is available at a six-month subscription for Rs 1,499. At the end of this period, three-month renewable subscriptions will be available. 																								 Areva will set up a high-voltage manufacturing plant at Padappai near Chennai. The unit will be an extension of its Perrungudi plant.																								 Intel Corporation has introduced a range of servers and PC processors. The processors do not have lead and halogen compounds in their components.																								 LG Electronics India has launched USB Plus TV for Rs 18,000. The product can be connected with digital devices like multimedia cards, USB thumb drive, MP3 player, PCs, cameras and iPods. ADVERTISEMENT
